\begin{abstract}
This is a research announcement concerning a series of constructions obtained by applying the ``doubling method"
from the theory of automorphic forms to covering groups.  Using these constructions, we obtain partial
tensor product $L$-functions attached to generalized Shimura lifts, which may be defined in a natural way
since at almost all places the representations are unramified principal series.
\end{abstract}

