\section{Introduction}\label{intro}
In their famous paper {\sl $L$-Functions for the Classical Groups} (in \cite{G-PS-R}), Piatetski-Shapiro and
Rallis introduced a new type of global integral which
represents the standard $L$-function for any split classical group. To
describe their construction, let ${{\mathbb{A}}}$ denote the ring of adeles
of a global field $F$. Let $G$ denote any split classical group,
$\pi_1$ and $\pi_2$ denote two irreducible cuspidal automorphic
representations of $G({{\mathbb{A}}})$, and $\varphi_{\pi_1},\varphi_{\pi_2}$
be automorphic forms in the corresponding spaces. Then the global integral they introduced
